51
00:01:20,824 --> 00:01:22,225
So Madam Mayor and members of the committee,

52
00:01:22,890 --> 00:01:30,595
Distributed to you this evening a report on the call that was received at Ventric High School this morning at about 9 o'clock.

53
00:01:31,556 --> 00:01:33,917
It was a robo call, an automated call.

54
00:01:33,937 --> 00:01:38,220
About eight other school districts in the area received the same call.

55
00:01:39,281 --> 00:01:43,123
Most of them stayed in place and didn't respond to it.

56
00:01:43,343 --> 00:01:50,628
We have had extensive discussions with state police, fire, and others about the appropriate responses to these matters.

57
00:01:52,330 --> 00:02:00,151
have given you the Massachusetts State Police bomb threat, if you will, a short guide as to how we handle these things.

58
00:02:01,292 --> 00:02:05,112
And on Thursday last, we actually had a workshop on it.

59
00:02:05,592 --> 00:02:09,653
We will be continuing to talk about these things because they could become more frequent.

60
00:02:10,453 --> 00:02:17,094
The one thing we can't let happen is we can't let people who are just mischievous just simply disrupt everyday school.

61
00:02:17,334 --> 00:02:21,295
And this will happen throughout the Commonwealth if we just simply need to react.

62
00:02:22,317 --> 00:02:31,161
On the other hand, it's critical that we evaluate every threat with great seriousness, and we do a thorough assessment.

63
00:02:31,801 --> 00:02:34,002
After we got the threat, we did a sweep of the building.

64
00:02:34,022 --> 00:02:36,243
We used other methodologies to book.

65
00:02:36,283 --> 00:02:39,324
We used our cameras and other things to see if anything unusual was around.

66
00:02:40,165 --> 00:02:43,346
And we determined that this was really not a high-level threat.

67
00:02:43,386 --> 00:02:44,467
It was a very low-level threat.

68
00:02:45,507 --> 00:02:48,508
And we put it out and moved on.

69
00:02:49,029 --> 00:02:51,850
Since that time, the headmaster has notified the faculty and students.

70
00:02:53,016 --> 00:03:00,139
Headmaster is sending out a robocall to parents this evening, which will tell them how it was handled and what was going on.

71
00:03:01,079 --> 00:03:06,581
So this seems to be the latest in the forms of school disruption that's taking place.

72
00:03:07,101 --> 00:03:08,502
We won't take anything seriously.

73
00:03:08,542 --> 00:03:13,704
If we think something is a little bit more involved, we will take it seriously and act appropriately.

74
00:03:13,724 --> 00:03:19,846
I don't want to discuss too much right now because I don't want to let anybody know all the trigger points that we would have.

75
00:03:22,820 --> 00:03:33,508
I have tentatively scheduled with your approval on February 10th a meeting with the police department and other school and community safety officials for the purposes of talking about school security and safety.

76
00:03:34,169 --> 00:03:38,952
That was the first night that everyone could agree on, which was February 10th.

77
00:03:39,012 --> 00:03:39,573
It's a Wednesday.

78
00:03:40,594 --> 00:03:42,535
Now we'll schedule other meetings as we go forward.

79
00:03:42,575 --> 00:03:50,321
It'll be a committee of the whole and topics like this will come up and we'll hear from the professionals as to why they feel one way or another when these things come in.

80
00:03:51,623 --> 00:03:53,344
So I'm happy to take any questions you may have.

81
00:03:54,625 --> 00:04:02,549
Otherwise, we'll continue to follow our protocols and continue to consult with police, fire, and other public safety officials.

82
00:04:03,510 --> 00:04:06,552
Mr. Benedetto, through you to the superintendent.

83
00:04:07,012 --> 00:04:12,275
