93
00:04:36,126 --> 00:04:43,129
We'll show you some things, I need to be careful that are not up to the general public, because I don't want people gaming our protocols.

94
00:04:43,569 --> 00:04:47,791
And did we do an auto call to a reverse call to our parents?

95
00:04:47,831 --> 00:04:52,973
Headmaster sent an auto call out, and sent one out this afternoon to- Just so parents are aware that this is happening.

96
00:04:52,993 --> 00:04:56,215
Yeah, I got a call, Erin, before I left the house, and my parents- Point of information, Ms.

97
00:04:56,235 --> 00:04:56,355
Pritz?

98
00:04:57,229 --> 00:04:58,329
Yes, point of information.

99
00:04:59,049 --> 00:05:01,610
That's great, I'm glad to hear that.

100
00:05:01,650 --> 00:05:06,651
Communication is key in these situations when safety of people's children are involved.

101
00:05:07,191 --> 00:05:11,732
So I think that that should be one of our main things when we have this situation going on.

102
00:05:11,772 --> 00:05:15,572
And then parents can make choices based on what they're comfortable with as well.

103
00:05:15,932 --> 00:05:23,674
What we've said before, and I'll say it again, it's very important that we don't, like at 9 o'clock, get it over with and suck on our parents because we want people coming up.

104
00:05:24,432 --> 00:05:26,554
And that creates more confusion and more chaos.

105
00:05:27,154 --> 00:05:34,461
If we felt there was any kind of danger, we wouldn't wait to move parents into the place, we'd be moving the youngsters very quickly.

106
00:05:35,602 --> 00:05:44,569
But there's a need to maintain calm, there's a need to maintain composure, and for everyone to act professionally when these things happen.

107
00:05:44,609 --> 00:05:47,392
Otherwise, you create more problems than you solve.

108
00:05:48,233 --> 00:05:51,534
And then everyone starts to, you know, think, well, gee, we can disrupt the place.

109
00:05:51,994 --> 00:05:55,995
Years ago, pulling fire alarms was a sport in most high schools.

110
00:05:56,675 --> 00:05:59,635
You know, people would pull the fire alarms, and everyone would have to do it.

111
00:05:59,676 --> 00:06:03,476
Now, back then, they weren't the bomb threats, the shooter threats, and things that we have today.

112
00:06:04,216 --> 00:06:06,657
But the same principle applies.

113
00:06:07,277 --> 00:06:15,459
If we let people continuously disrupt our operations without good cause, without real understanding of what's taking place, then we just play into their hands.

114
