00:49:35,971 --> 00:49:48,180
And then I've attached the actual visual of the accountability system which shows school districts in different levels and what we're obliged to do when you're in different levels.

611
00:49:50,702 --> 00:49:54,064
And then I've also attached to a couple of sheets of data.

612
00:49:55,145 --> 00:49:56,986
Again, I have a folder.

613
00:49:57,026 --> 00:49:58,347
I have it with me if you want me to go through it.

614
00:49:58,767 --> 00:50:00,689
I have packets of materials like this.

615
00:50:01,431 --> 00:50:04,152
just more and more, you can just dig all this stuff out.

616
00:50:04,172 --> 00:50:09,934
But I wanted to share with you some of the things that I saw and, you know, Bernadette and the other members of our team saw.

617
00:50:10,534 --> 00:50:25,919
If you go to the sheet on the accountability data from Medford, you can see for yourself that the numbers, so for example, if we look at English Language Arts and we look at that first category, narrowing the proficiency gap, we actually got more points than in past years.

618
00:50:26,899 --> 00:50:29,880
So if you go down there, you'll see some very solid gains.

619
00:50:30,881 --> 00:50:32,401
elaborating on each one.

620
00:50:33,262 --> 00:50:43,265
Again, I point out the ELL, the bonus points, the 25 points, the progress that's being made in both English and mathematics, all right?

621
00:50:44,025 --> 00:50:54,468
And again, it doesn't look, if you look at the data that we've really regressed, but remember the problem is the bar keeps getting higher and higher.

622
00:50:54,828 --> 00:50:57,989
And if they change things like what subgroups are being reported out,

623
00:50:58,718 --> 00:51:00,920
That adds another problem to the mix.

624
00:51:01,820 --> 00:51:11,828
And even if you look at the data for the Roberts, again, it's in some categories consistent, in some categories higher than it was in previous years.

625
00:51:12,629 --> 00:51:14,830
And yet their rating was a level three.

626
00:51:15,771 --> 00:51:23,197
Again, their subgroup, the ELL students, were one of the subgroups that didn't make the target, but bonus points for access.

627
00:51:24,102 --> 00:51:27,643
So you figure, I can't, you know, I've been in this business 46 years.

628
00:51:27,683 --> 00:51:28,683
I'm having trouble with this one.

629
00:51:29,183 --> 00:51:29,743
I really am.

630
00:51:29,823 --> 00:51:36,805
So the other thing is that I mentioned before that students can be in multiple categories.

631
00:51:37,445 --> 00:51:42,066
So we could have an ELL student who score is involved in other categories.

632
00:51:42,927 --> 00:51:48,868
And the other thing too is remember that subgroups are based on self-identification.

633
00:51:49,761 --> 00:51:52,522
So how do we get students into a subgroup?

634
00:51:52,782 --> 00:52:01,264
When a student enrolls in the school district, and they enroll at the Parent Information Center, the parent selects the subgroups.

635
00:52:01,684 --> 00:52:04,985
So again, that's how the process is.

636
00:52:05,065 --> 00:52:07,886
It's not that the state monitors who's in what subgroup.

637
00:52:07,946 --> 00:52:09,846
It's a self-selecting process.

638
00:52:10,746 --> 00:52:13,107
So with that, I will answer any questions that I can.

639
00:52:14,096 --> 00:52:17,738
I'm still waiting for answers myself, but we'll keep you informed.

640
00:52:17,818 --> 00:52:22,341
And we just really want to know, what do we have to do to move up?

641
00:52:22,641 --> 00:52:24,102
Because we've been very solid.

642
00:52:24,122 --> 00:52:25,063
We've seen gains.

643
00:52:25,623 --> 00:52:27,645
This is very frustrating for all of our people.

644
00:52:27,685 --> 00:52:28,905
They've worked very, very hard.

645
00:52:29,286 --> 00:52:37,731
And the directors of humanities and math, when they sat there initially with the DESE people and they said, we got no credit for moving kids from needs improvement to proficient.

646
00:52:38,197 --> 00:52:40,699
That's what we were supposed to be doing, and we've been working hard doing that.

