00:52:41,639 --> 00:52:44,681
That's what the MCAS Academy money, grant money is for, to do that.

648
00:52:45,281 --> 00:52:47,903
And yet, hello, nothing there.

649
00:52:47,923 --> 00:52:50,024
So anyway, so if I can take any questions.

650
00:52:50,205 --> 00:52:50,845
Mr. Skerry.

651
00:52:51,085 --> 00:52:56,388
Mayor, I read through this report three times Friday night, and it seems to be everything's going into a circle.

652
00:52:56,408 --> 00:53:03,653
You know, we have a dedicated cadre of teachers and administrators that year in, year out go through this.

653
00:53:04,413 --> 00:53:06,695
And I'm just hard to see that whenever

654
00:53:07,232 --> 00:53:10,173
The State Department of Education waxes, it's always the same school.

655
00:53:10,633 --> 00:53:14,135
And I know that we've made great strides there.

656
00:53:15,155 --> 00:53:21,338
I would suggest through you to the superintendent, Mrs. Nelson, that perhaps Mrs. Jackman and Ms.

657
00:53:21,358 --> 00:53:28,100
Bresnahan would like to come to a meeting and explain this to us and break it down and see just exactly why we're at where we're at.

658
00:53:28,781 --> 00:53:32,602
And there are a lot of things in here that are misnomers and I'd like them cleared up.

659
00:53:32,942 --> 00:53:34,823
I think we owe that to our kids.

660
00:53:35,555 --> 00:53:37,936
And we owe it to the citizens of Medford, they're our taxpayers.

661
00:53:38,536 --> 00:53:42,117
I just don't think the way that they're doing things is the correct way to do things.

662
00:53:42,197 --> 00:53:48,099
And I'm tired of Medford being misaligned when I know that our kids are working hard to improve themselves.

663
00:53:48,540 --> 00:53:53,481
And our teachers and again, administrators are working to put everybody on the same playing field.

664
00:53:53,541 --> 00:54:00,744
And this report and what they're doing to Medford is not what we expected, it's not what we deserve, and it's not what our kids deserve.

665
00:54:01,280 --> 00:54:13,374
They're doing it to everybody, and I think one of the things that's very telling about our school district is that there are many school districts and many schools, high schools, and affluent communities that are not level one.

666
00:54:13,874 --> 00:54:20,242
I know Bernadette, you may have some of that data to share, but some of the communities that we tout as the, you know,

667
00:54:21,182 --> 00:54:26,586
better economically situated communities and kids do better than they do not at the high school level.

668
00:54:27,026 --> 00:54:28,508
So Bernadette, do you want to share some of that?

669
00:54:28,568 --> 00:54:30,189
Just one last comment, Billie.

670
00:54:30,469 --> 00:54:35,052
If they're the district school assistance center, I think they should be here talking to us directly.

671
00:54:35,072 --> 00:54:36,854
And if we do have questions, let them answer.

672
00:54:36,874 --> 00:54:39,416
If they can't answer it, let them get back to us in a week.

673
00:54:40,554 --> 00:54:42,935
let this go on forever and ever in infinity.

674
00:54:42,955 --> 00:54:52,259
I had one question that was, what do we need, what one point where do we need that one point, because they were one point away from making level two.

675
00:54:52,379 --> 00:54:56,842
And if it's one point away, in all courses of life, you have recourse.

676
00:54:57,582 --> 00:55:03,925
And, you know, perhaps they better check their figures again and look at some of the answers and really try to get into what's happening here.

677
00:55:04,245 --> 00:55:06,426
Because I don't, you know, year after year they misalign.

678
00:55:07,180 --> 00:55:10,521
you know, a certain school, and it's not fair to the kids or the teachers in that school.

679
00:55:11,441 --> 00:55:18,763
We, we do, excuse me, but we do question the numbers because one of the things we did is there were, I think, 26 ELL students reported out.

680
00:55:18,803 --> 00:55:27,205
And when Leslie Trotta went back and she examined the kids who were actually tested, because we had the names and the numbers, it didn't come out to that.

681
00:55:27,746 --> 00:55:32,747
One of the things that we thought was really very perplexing that we did discover, and that is that

682
00:55:33,379 --> 00:55:37,542
ELL students have to take mathematics, even if they arrive the day before the test.

683
00:55:37,782 --> 00:55:43,567
Okay, English, they get a year kind of off to learn the language, although you need a lot more than a year.

684
00:55:44,187 --> 00:55:52,994
But we found out that they had those math, they had those kids take that math test, and they didn't count them in the school's results, they counted them in the district results.

685
00:55:53,635 --> 00:55:54,155
Go figure.

686
00:55:54,648 --> 00:55:56,749
It's like I said, it's not an even playing field.

687
00:55:56,769 --> 00:55:57,890
And I think Ms.

688
00:55:57,930 --> 00:55:58,691
Jackman and Ms.

689
00:55:58,731 --> 00:56:05,575
Bresnahan should be here in this forum to explain to us their reasoning and how they come about with what they have to do.

690
00:56:05,595 --> 00:56:07,676
I mean, they have to be held accountable.

691
00:56:08,077 --> 00:56:09,538
We should hold their feet to the fire.

692
00:56:11,976 --> 00:56:14,057
So just to add to that, good evening.

693
00:56:15,017 --> 00:56:22,379
To add to what Beverly was just saying, also what we found missing was rating on two of our subgroups.

694
00:56:22,459 --> 00:56:25,900
The Hispanic Latino subgroup for the Roberts Elementary was missing.

695
00:56:26,180 --> 00:56:30,941
There was a population there, but it did not get configured into the accountability result.

696
00:56:31,021 --> 00:56:36,183
And the other subgroup was the African, it wasn't the African American, I think it was Asian, that's right.

697
00:56:36,703 --> 00:56:39,245
So two subgroups, we had missing data.

698
00:56:39,325 --> 00:56:41,466
So we did pose that question to Ms.

699
00:56:41,506 --> 00:56:42,126
Bresnahan.

700
00:56:42,627 --> 00:56:44,148
She did not have an answer for us.

701
00:56:44,168 --> 00:56:45,889
So that's one of the things that we're waiting on.

702
00:56:45,909 --> 00:56:50,832
It'd be great to say that they just left the data out and that that would help us.

703
00:56:50,852 --> 00:56:54,454
Um, but we, we are waiting to get an answer on that.

704
00:56:55,655 --> 00:56:57,276
I think two weeks is a long time to wait.

705
00:56:57,316 --> 00:56:57,696
Mr. Cadelli.

706
00:56:59,015 --> 00:57:01,317
I mean, kids' futures are at stake here.

707
00:57:01,597 --> 00:57:03,138
We don't know how to make them better.

708
00:57:03,538 --> 00:57:06,580
And if they're not going to help us, why go through this rigmarole?

709
00:57:07,401 --> 00:57:14,286
So we have a tentative meeting scheduled for next Monday, February 8th, to talk to Ms.

710
00:57:14,326 --> 00:57:15,186
Jackman and Ms.

711
00:57:15,206 --> 00:57:15,747
Bresnahan.

712
00:57:17,183 --> 00:57:28,328
there is the possibility they may be working with us in our professional development day, so we will be meeting with them tentatively next Monday, hoping to get some answers on that day, if not before.

713
00:57:28,348 --> 00:57:32,910
I'd like them to come in and explain their reasoning to this August body, our next school committee meeting.

714
00:57:32,930 --> 00:57:35,612
I mean, I take this very seriously.

715
00:57:37,742 --> 00:57:50,671
If we were going to do that, I'd much prefer it to be at a committee of the whole and a different, this environment is not conducive to the sort of data analysis that we would need to do.

716
00:57:50,751 --> 00:57:53,673
So I would suggest a committee of the whole if we were to go that path.

717
00:57:55,214 --> 00:57:56,435
So let me, let me just say this.

718
00:57:57,596 --> 00:57:59,717
This system is very, very involved.

719
00:58:00,818 --> 00:58:02,559
It was created as a compromise.

720
00:58:04,148 --> 00:58:07,230
to deal with the federal government that was trying to change its positions.

721
00:58:08,050 --> 00:58:21,938
And you notice a new act came through this past year, E-S-S-A, which changed the basis for the waiver system that the then Secretary of Education, Arne Duncan, put in place, and the state got a waiver on it.

722
00:58:22,318 --> 00:58:31,644
And in order for the state to get the waiver the second time around, they had to make the system more rigorous and move away from what E-S-S-A says it's trying to do.

723
00:58:32,324 --> 00:58:33,765
So that begs a question to begin with.

724
00:58:34,540 --> 00:58:35,780
I would just suggest the following.

725
00:58:35,900 --> 00:58:38,782
First of all, let's not define ourselves by this particular system.

726
00:58:39,682 --> 00:58:41,542
We know there are good things happening.

727
00:58:41,703 --> 00:58:43,403
We know there are some things that need to be worked on.

728
00:58:44,624 --> 00:58:46,344
Most of our schools are doing just fine.

729
00:58:47,144 --> 00:58:56,188
If you look at some, as Beverly and Bernadette pointed out, some of the allegedly best high schools in the state, they're level two and our high school's level one.

730
00:58:57,008 --> 00:58:57,448
You know why?

731
00:58:58,288 --> 00:58:59,649
Because they haven't got less room to grow.

732
00:59:00,628 --> 00:59:03,909
their progress and their performance can only grow so high.

733
00:59:03,969 --> 00:59:05,349
So their progress is muted.

734
00:59:06,949 --> 00:59:14,050
Now, certain communities, which are way below us in terms of actual performance, became level two.

735
00:59:14,851 --> 00:59:15,131
Why?

736
00:59:15,671 --> 00:59:19,991
Because they can show progress from the depths up a little bit more, so they get more points.

737
00:59:21,072 --> 00:59:22,792
The system fights each other.

738
00:59:22,832 --> 00:59:24,392
There are two basic issues.

739
00:59:24,832 --> 00:59:28,633
The CPI, the cumulative performance index,

740
00:59:29,403 --> 00:59:33,286
which is based on so many points per scoring at each level.

741
00:59:34,087 --> 00:59:43,393
Advanced and Proficient getting 100, Needs Improvement getting either 75 or 50, depending on what level of Needs Improvement you are, and then less down below.

742
00:59:44,594 --> 00:59:48,217
Now, we do just fine on the CPI.

743
00:59:49,658 --> 00:59:53,821
And in fact, we're ahead of some communities that in fact got a better accountability rating.

744
00:59:54,802 --> 00:59:58,705
But they've got more room to grow in terms of progress from down here.

745
01:00:00,217 --> 01:00:04,738
The performance index deals primarily with growth.

746
01:00:05,759 --> 01:00:17,042
Now, if they're going to change the numbers of people in a group and try to compare them year to year, you would fail a statistics course at any local university.

747
01:00:17,062 --> 01:00:19,222
You just don't do that.

748
01:00:19,862 --> 01:00:22,983
So I brought it to the attention of the association.

749
01:00:23,523 --> 01:00:25,304
I'll continue to bring it to the attention.

750
01:00:25,504 --> 01:00:27,504
There'll be a robust discussion on the thing.

751
01:00:27,864 --> 01:00:29,585
The people who are representing the department,

752
01:00:30,575 --> 01:00:32,276
quite frankly, are really just messengers.

753
01:00:33,077 --> 01:00:34,338
They can only tell you so much.

754
01:00:35,019 --> 01:00:46,929
We really need to get into the people to design these things, and that's best done initially at the association level where we can get them there and really grill it and really talk about more than one district at a time.

755
01:00:46,949 --> 01:00:49,491
If you're talking about one district, some of you think you're whining.

756
01:00:49,971 --> 01:00:54,115
If you're talking about multiple districts, it looks like, what do you call it, you're saying, this is a problem.

757
01:00:54,635 --> 01:00:58,899
So if you take a look at a place like Waltham, a lot of characteristics of that, same thing, drop down.

758
01:00:59,539 --> 01:01:01,220
Reading, same thing, dropped down.

759
01:01:01,840 --> 01:01:04,981
A lot of places have similar kind of experiences.

760
01:01:05,521 --> 01:01:10,542
So I'm not going to define this school district by this particular rating.

761
01:01:11,183 --> 01:01:13,503
I'm pleased that the high school and the vocational are level one.

762
01:01:13,523 --> 01:01:17,484
I'm pleased that the other schools are holding their own for the purposes of explaining it.

763
01:01:18,705 --> 01:01:28,988
But we're not going to accept the fact that the system applied measures that don't ring true to any kind of statistical analysis that we're aware of.

764
01:01:29,675 --> 01:01:35,578
or they change the formula without giving proper notice to the districts of how the formula was going to change.

765
01:01:36,498 --> 01:01:38,979
So we'll get back into it.

766
01:01:39,139 --> 01:01:41,721
Just don't beat yourself up on it.

767
01:01:41,741 --> 01:01:43,862
Understand that it's a complex area.

768
01:01:44,742 --> 01:01:47,243
Understand that we're committed to doing well by all our students.

769
01:01:47,924 --> 01:01:53,466
Understand there's complexity in taking tests, complexity in all the changes that are going on.

770
01:01:54,547 --> 01:01:57,268
And we're going to work our way through it, just like we work our way through everything.

771
01:01:58,138 --> 01:02:00,239
And in a real short time, we'll be back to you.

772
01:02:00,419 --> 01:02:06,041
I'm sure we're going to have some very interesting findings, along with some other districts that have similar experience.

773
01:02:06,722 --> 01:02:08,082
But we want to tell you the truth.

774
01:02:08,122 --> 01:02:14,585
We're out here tonight talking, giving you the information, because I wouldn't want you to read it in some other place and say, why didn't you tell us?

775
01:02:15,765 --> 01:02:22,928
But I'm relatively confident that this stuff is going to get a real scrutinization before it's over.

776
01:02:23,649 --> 01:02:27,190
And you should be generally pleased that

777
01:02:28,059 --> 01:02:34,362
high school and vocational school score higher than Andover and some other places.

778
01:02:35,042 --> 01:02:37,123
Arlington, okay, some other places.

779
01:02:37,323 --> 01:02:42,786
Maybe not Arlington, I may mix up one, but you know, score higher than some of these places.

780
01:02:43,146 --> 01:02:45,267
Bernadette has the list.

781
01:02:45,327 --> 01:02:49,509
All right, that's okay because, all right, so I have a few more communities.

782
01:02:49,989 --> 01:02:56,032
So we know that Medford High School and Medford Vocational Technical High School are level one schools.

783
01:02:57,253 --> 01:03:00,154
The following high schools are level two.

784
01:03:00,615 --> 01:03:06,397
Lexington High School, Andover High School, North Redding High School, Redding High School, and Wakefield High School.

785
01:03:06,697 --> 01:03:10,299
So they're level two, where Medford High School is level one.

786
01:03:10,859 --> 01:03:14,721
What I thought was surprising is I looked at district levels also.

787
01:03:15,281 --> 01:03:18,043
Redding actually is a level three district.

788
01:03:18,763 --> 01:03:20,804
So they're comparable to us in that rating.

789
01:03:20,984 --> 01:03:22,244
And Waltham's a level three.

790
01:03:22,325 --> 01:03:23,065
It's a high school, too.

791
01:03:24,125 --> 01:03:24,606
I'm sorry?

792
01:03:24,626 --> 01:03:25,426
It's Waltham, too.

793
01:03:25,960 --> 01:03:27,881
Waltham is also.

794
01:03:28,362 --> 01:03:38,369
The system may work mechanically, but it begs a question as to what it really tells you about actualities.

795
01:03:38,749 --> 01:03:41,851
And so, you know, we're giving you the information.

796
01:03:42,872 --> 01:03:45,134
We'll continue to research what we're doing.

797
01:03:45,174 --> 01:03:52,139
We'll continue to talk to our colleagues and we'll continue to pursue the department as to how they do this, because it's not just for this year, it's going forward.

798
01:03:52,879 --> 01:03:54,020
If you're going to rate schools,

799
01:03:54,732 --> 01:04:13,126
If you're going to rate programs, you've got to have something that's transparent and understandable, and something that enables each district to work on whatever might be considered a deficit in a meaningful and progressive way, not to be surprised at how you came up.

800
01:04:14,247 --> 01:04:21,052
You know, sometimes when you watch certain figure skating things or you wonder how the judges came up with something, well,

801
01:04:22,607 --> 01:04:28,350
I think we're saying things, if you watch a basketball game or a hockey game, you know the sport at the end of the game.

802
01:04:28,370 --> 01:04:29,251
Enough of the sports analysis.

803
01:04:29,291 --> 01:04:30,591
Thank you, Mr. Superintendent.

804
01:04:30,611 --> 01:04:30,651
Ms.

805
01:04:30,952 --> 01:04:33,193
Cunha, did you have a question?

806
01:04:33,233 --> 01:04:33,593
Yes.

807
01:04:35,734 --> 01:04:39,596
The whole report, I know the superintendent is saying not to get frustrated, but I'm frustrated.

808
01:04:41,697 --> 01:04:49,702
As he said, the commissioner of education has constantly said that he was definitely going to look at the formula of growth.

809
01:04:50,972 --> 01:04:53,773
And this has changed everything.

810
01:04:54,293 --> 01:05:01,697
How do you look at the formula of growth and not look at needs improvement to proficient and not scaleless with any extra points?

811
01:05:02,537 --> 01:05:04,678
Totally don't understand that at all.

812
01:05:05,258 --> 01:05:10,280
It's like he's changed the formula upside down without informing anyone at all.

813
01:05:10,801 --> 01:05:14,282
You can't change the formula in the middle of this at all.

814
01:05:14,922 --> 01:05:16,023
It does not make sense.

815
01:05:16,785 --> 01:05:20,946
And changing everything in the middle of students taking tests is just not fair.

816
01:05:21,086 --> 01:05:22,346
It's just not fair.

817
01:05:22,846 --> 01:05:40,910
So what I do suggest and advise maybe is just as much as you've reached out to the superintendents association is also to reach out to MASC and hopefully between the two associations try to get more support.

818
01:05:41,810 --> 01:05:46,033
And to try to look into the process of appeals, because this is definitely something that cannot.

819
01:05:46,053 --> 01:05:48,035
I mean, we can't sit back on this.

820
01:05:48,535 --> 01:05:57,602
And as you said, Superintendent, I'm sure we're not the only ones that have gone through this, and I'm sure we're not the only ones that are upset over something like this, because

821
01:05:58,220 --> 01:06:00,464
You can't change the playing field like this.

822
01:06:00,965 --> 01:06:08,076
You have students, administration, everyone investing into this and doing what is being asked of us.

823
01:06:08,897 --> 01:06:11,562
And then in the middle of it, you just change it all?

824
01:06:13,335 --> 01:06:14,135
It's just not right.

825
01:06:14,555 --> 01:06:15,956
It's just absolutely not right.

826
01:06:16,036 --> 01:06:25,317
And it's very frustrating, especially when you see the commissioner and he stands there and he tells you that this is how we're all going to work together and this is how we're all going to do it.

827
01:06:25,877 --> 01:06:27,858
And then it seems like it's a slap in the face.

828
01:06:29,118 --> 01:06:31,058
Very frustrating.

829
01:06:32,418 --> 01:06:33,579
Thank you, Madam Mayor.

830
01:06:34,119 --> 01:06:35,699
I'm too troubled by this.

831
01:06:35,959 --> 01:06:42,300
Partly my biggest concern is how does it, how is it going to be interpreted by the parents of the Roberts?

832
01:06:42,888 --> 01:06:49,614
because as a parent of the Roberts, I would assume that, you know, it would be, it's very complex information.

833
01:06:49,694 --> 01:07:04,105
We sound as if, you know, we're trying to make excuses because after all, this is the, you know, report we're getting, but we understand all the technicalities involved, but that's hard to translate.

834
01:07:04,826 --> 01:07:12,252
And so I would, I know that a letter needs to go out to the parents of the Roberts, and I just hope that that is well crafted and that,

835
01:07:12,628 --> 01:07:18,450
If there needs to be subsequent meetings with the parents to reassure them, that you will obviously do that.

836
01:07:18,470 --> 01:07:19,830
I have no doubt that you will.

837
01:07:19,850 --> 01:07:27,692
So what I suggested to you was, is that in the near future, very near future, I'm actually going down to the school and run a little open forum with them.

838
01:07:28,432 --> 01:07:34,874
And we answer their questions, come down and talk about the good things going on at the Roberts and talk about the anomalies of the system.

839
01:07:35,380 --> 01:07:37,081
Will you let us know when that's going to take place?

840
01:07:37,462 --> 01:07:39,263
Yeah, I think that's a good idea.

841
01:07:40,584 --> 01:07:42,686
Again, totally concerned about this.

842
01:07:43,147 --> 01:07:45,529
Does this rating now stand for two years?

843
01:07:45,629 --> 01:07:48,992
Is there still a two-year cycle that there used to be?

844
01:07:50,881 --> 01:07:59,707
Ratings have gone year to year, but now where we're going to be taking the park, we're held harmless, which means we can't go down, not that we would.

845
01:08:00,528 --> 01:08:02,649
If we do better, we can go up.

846
01:08:02,829 --> 01:08:03,810
So it's a year to year.

847
01:08:03,830 --> 01:08:04,931
It's an annual rating.

848
01:08:05,411 --> 01:08:12,436
And the other concern, of course, is the one you mentioned about the cohorts of the number of kids changing and that a child can be in multiple cohorts.

849
01:08:12,883 --> 01:08:19,445
If you have a child who's truly struggling, that means, you know, if there's only 20 kids, that's a significant change.

850
01:08:19,525 --> 01:08:23,285
And, you know, if you have one or two kids, that is going to change your numbers significantly.

851
01:08:23,826 --> 01:08:27,066
It should be noted that the state never meets its own targets.

852
01:08:28,807 --> 01:08:29,647
It sets targets.

853
01:08:29,827 --> 01:08:32,848
It's yet to meet its own targets in some of these special populations.

854
