That's the money that we get for buses that go to Minneapolis.

1117
01:27:28,061 --> 01:27:32,282
That will offset Minuteman's bus as it has this year at about 50% of the cost.

1118
01:27:32,362 --> 01:27:33,783
Bus costs about $65,000, okay?

1119
01:27:35,943 --> 01:27:40,304
Homeless transportation is level funded when we pay a portion of the anticipated liability.

1120
01:27:40,744 --> 01:27:44,345
And it always depends on how many are homeless across the state and for men.

1121
01:27:45,486 --> 01:27:47,746
The more homeless, the bigger the bill.

1122
01:27:47,786 --> 01:27:50,187
The more transportation, the bigger the bill.

1123
01:27:51,987 --> 01:27:58,212
The more across the state, the less distribution, because there's only a limited amount of money, so the percentage distributed comes down.

1124
01:27:58,872 --> 01:28:02,615
But it's only projected about half of the anticipated liability.

1125
01:28:03,996 --> 01:28:07,219
Charter school funding is a real sleight of hand proposal.

1126
01:28:07,960 --> 01:28:12,964
This year, the line item was $54 million below the formula for reimbursement.

1127
01:28:12,984 --> 01:28:14,925
$54 million below the formula for reimbursement.

1128
01:28:15,666 --> 01:28:20,710
