1131
01:28:38,222 --> 01:28:38,962
That would be Medford.

1132
01:28:40,103 --> 01:28:41,463
We would lose substantial money.

1133
01:28:44,145 --> 01:28:50,288
Depending on your communities, charter enrollment, and economic disadvantage, which we're not economically disadvantaged in terms of the state.

1134
01:28:51,150 --> 01:28:57,354
This proposed method would cost Medford reimbursement funding over the next few years, and obviously we should strongly oppose it.

1135
01:28:57,374 --> 01:29:04,920
We're having discussions in the Senate where the opposition seems to be stronger.

1136
01:29:05,460 --> 01:29:11,885
The House seems to be in favor of some form of charter lift, but I need to find out what specifically they're going to go for.

1137
01:29:11,965 --> 01:29:17,849
As you know, there's a petition out there that will be in the election next year if this legislation doesn't pass.

1138
01:29:19,996 --> 01:29:24,618
In the current tense, the projected net charter cost increase over last year could be as much as $547,611.

1139
01:29:24,678 --> 01:29:37,362
Furthermore, DESE may allow Mystic Valley to grow its enrollment by 400 students, probably not all in one year, and this could obviously affect us.

1140
01:29:39,163 --> 01:29:48,186
Now, the reason for that is DESE restricted Mystic Valley because it wasn't taking in ELL students or a sufficiently diverse population

1141
01:29:48,562 --> 01:29:51,683
and its governance structure was considered to be less than favorable.

1142
01:29:53,144 --> 01:29:55,545
For some reason, the commissioner is saying, well, they've made progress.

1143
01:29:56,285 --> 01:29:58,746
My read of their version of progress isn't very high.

1144
01:30:00,506 --> 01:30:04,368
But if they're allowed to take more students, that could impact us.

1145
01:30:05,788 --> 01:30:07,229
And that means the numbers go up.

1146
01:30:08,209 --> 01:30:10,170
And that means there's less reimbursement.

1147
01:30:10,510 --> 01:30:12,811
And that means it takes dollars away from the locality.

1148
01:30:13,091 --> 01:30:16,112
This is a major fight that has to happen on the Hill.

1149
01:30:17,883 --> 01:30:20,424
Special education circuit breaker funding is level funding.

1150
01:30:21,245 --> 01:30:24,446
These cost factors for extraordinary placement and spend inevitably go up.

1151
01:30:24,466 --> 01:30:33,490
It's probably $11 to $12 million lower than what the Circuit Breaker Coalition, of which I serve on, anticipates the next year.

1152
01:30:34,431 --> 01:30:37,712
These are the costs of private day placements and residential placements.

1153
01:30:38,673 --> 01:30:40,373
Now, it's a mixed bag.

1154
01:30:41,254 --> 01:30:45,716
Obviously, we want the money for this, but I'm also very concerned that

1155
01:30:46,261 --> 01:30:52,304
In some of these places, the private schools are just simply trying to raise their tuition costs or adding to it.

1156
01:30:52,344 --> 01:30:54,805
So we need to have a bigger discussion about that.

1157
01:30:54,865 --> 01:30:57,046
Plus the fact transportation in schools is not funded.

1158
01:30:58,266 --> 01:31:02,168
And we think that sometimes can be as expensive as the other.

1159
01:31:03,108 --> 01:31:06,850
The Department of Public Health School Health Services grant is also level funding.

1160
01:31:06,870 --> 01:31:11,552
And we can expect a small reduction in that distribution if the governor's budget were sustained.

1161
01:31:13,018 --> 01:31:16,380
That pays for school nurse and a few other school related activities.

1162
01:31:18,321 --> 01:31:25,706
School choice costs in FY17 are projected at 62,000 versus 16,712 in FY16.

1163
01:31:26,046 --> 01:31:27,487
That number could change three or four times.

1164
01:31:28,107 --> 01:31:29,908
So I'm not so sure how that's going to play out.

1165
01:31:29,928 --> 01:31:32,710
Those are just estimates based on what they think might move.

1166
01:31:33,551 --> 01:31:40,675
So it's not something to be ignored, but I don't think it may hold because every year it's a little different.

1167
01:31:42,023 --> 01:31:47,444
The early education and care department funds some of our early childhood operations.

1168
01:31:47,504 --> 01:31:48,924
There are several programs involved.

1169
01:31:48,985 --> 01:31:56,286
The governors consolidate some of the funding streams, so it's unclear which programs will benefit and which ones will be cut.

1170
01:31:56,966 --> 01:31:59,787
This needs to be fleshed out over the next deliberative period.

1171
01:32:00,347 --> 01:32:06,608
The Children's Trust Fund, which funds a good part of the family network, a major contributor to our family, is level funding.

1172
01:32:07,388 --> 01:32:09,249
They're trying to do more, and hopefully

1173
01:32:10,089 --> 01:32:18,956
They get more because they're a very good program, but if they get level funding and more and more programs come in, then they cut back what they can give to any one program.

