There are some schools out there that take youngsters in on school choice because it fills empty seats and they get five, $6,000, depending on whether special needs or not, and it gives them a certain amount of money.

1185
01:33:36,742 --> 01:33:38,322
It's a very low amount of money.

1186
01:33:38,902 --> 01:33:43,966
And if a youngster has certain needs and the like, it could very well be losing financial proposition.

